Vanessa Jones' oldest child was regularly falling asleep to the television, and her youngest begged to go to Dairy Queen to get a toy advertised on TV. This weekend they are getting some help from an unlikely source : Nickelodeon, the No. 1 network for children, is replacing its usual Saturday afternoon lineup with a message encouraging young viewers to go outside and play. Marva Smalls, executive vice president for public affairs at Nickelodeon, acknowledged that awareness about childhood obesity is up, but said the network's initiatives were not a response to outside pressure. 